<subSubSection lastPageId="81" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="80.[151,1437,1430,2033]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1647,1673]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Remarks</emphasis>
. This is a member of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linne" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[588,724,1647,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvaticus">
<emphasis box="[588,724,1647,1673]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">P. sylvaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[926,1126,1646,1673]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" pagination="323 - 351" refId="ref76025" refString="Shinohara, A. (1985 a) Web-spinning sawflies of the sylvaticus group of Pamphilius (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Systematic Entomology, 10, 323 - 351. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1985. tb 00141. x" type="journal article" year="1985">
Shinohara (1985 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1113,1126,1646,1673]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 2002b). 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1230,1436,1647,1673]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" pagination="307 - 320" refId="ref76348" refString="Shinohara, A. (1988 a) The group of Pamphilius sylvaticus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae): Five new species and additional records from the Far East. Kontyu, Tokyo, 56, 307 - 320." type="journal article" year="1988">Shinohara (1988a)</bibRefCitation>
described this subspecies as a full species but 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[662,857,1683,1709]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" pagination="99 - 116" refId="ref76721" refString="Shinohara, A. (2001) The group of Pamphilius sylvaticus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae): Two new species, new collection records, and a key to Palearctic species. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 7, 99 - 116." type="journal article" year="2001">Shinohara (2001)</bibRefCitation>
treated it as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1985" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[1173,1309,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">P. montanus</emphasis>
Shinohara, 1985
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="80.[151,1437,1430,2033]" lastBlockId="81.[151,1436,151,321]" lastPageId="81" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
In our molecular analysis, the maximum intrasubspecific 
<emphasis box="[837,851,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">p</emphasis>
-distance among specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1223,1291,1755,1781]" name="South Korea" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Korea</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingRegion country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[193,260,1791,1817]" name="Japan" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Japan</collectingCountry>
, was 1.5% in COI (n=4) and 0.2% in NaK (n=3). The minimum distance to the specimens of the nominotypical 
<taxonomicName box="[234,486,1827,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="montanus" subSpecies="montanus">
<emphasis box="[234,486,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">P. montanus montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Honshu, 
<collectingCountry box="[654,721,1827,1853]" name="Japan" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Japan</collectingCountry>
, was 3.7% in COI and 0.1% in NaK. The nearest neighbour was 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[151,268,1863,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volatilis">
<emphasis box="[151,268,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">P. volatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, diverging by a minimum of 4.1% in the COI analysis, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ermolenko" authorityYear="1973" box="[933,1052,1863,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alnicola">
<emphasis box="[933,1052,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">P. alnicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, diverging by a minimum of 0.6% in the NaK analysis. In the COI tree (
<figureCitation box="[562,659,1898,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 145" captionStartId="232.[151,250,1669,1693]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-26@232.[151,1436,181,1645]" captionTargetPageId="232" captionText="FIGURE 145. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius sylvaticus group, part 1." pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Fig. 145</figureCitation>
), each of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[765,901,1899,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[765,901,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">P. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[914,1083,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
P. m. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[974,1083,1899,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">montanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1135,1281,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
P. m. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[1195,1281,1899,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcher">pulcher</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was retrieved as monophyletic with UFBoot support of 100% and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[759,898,1935,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[759,898,1935,1960]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">P. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ermolenko" authorityYear="1973" box="[1061,1183,1935,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alnicola">
<emphasis box="[1061,1183,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">P. alnicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with UFBoot support of 82%. In the NaK tree (
<figureCitation box="[442,540,1970,1997]" captionStart="FIGURE 159" captionStartId="244.[151,250,1756,1780]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,187,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-26@244.[151,1436,181,1733]" captionTargetPageId="244" captionText="FIGURE 159. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius sylvaticus group." pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Fig. 159</figureCitation>
), 
<emphasis box="[561,734,1971,1996]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
P. m. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[625,734,1971,1996]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">montanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(n=2) was retrieved as monophyletic with UFBoot support of 100%, but 
<emphasis box="[274,422,2007,2033]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
P. m. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[336,422,2007,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcher">pulcher</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(n=3) was not, while all the specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[901,1038,2007,2032]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[901,1038,2007,2032]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">P. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(n=5) formed a clade with UFBoot support of 93% and the clade consisting of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[635,748,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[635,748,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">P. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Kramp &amp; Taeger" authorityYear="2022" box="[802,955,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graciloides">
<emphasis box="[802,955,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">P. graciloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was retrieved as sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[1243,1380,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[1243,1380,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">P. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with very low UFBoot support of 70%.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="81.[151,1436,151,321]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="2001" box="[199,534,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="montanus" subSpecies="pulcher">
<emphasis box="[199,534,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Pamphilius montanus pulcher</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably associated with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Shinohara &amp; Hara" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[847,925,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[847,925,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Sorbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[939,1048,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
) because the larvae of the nominotypical subspecies from Honshu, 
<collectingCountry box="[521,588,259,285]" name="Japan" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Japan</collectingCountry>
, are gregarious web-spinners on 
<taxonomicName authority="Hedl." authorityName="Hedl." box="[954,1216,259,285]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="commixta">
<emphasis box="[954,1147,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Sorbus commixta</emphasis>
Hedl.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1229,1338,259,285]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kojima, H." pageId="81" pageNumber="82" pagination="27 - 33" refId="ref78349" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kojima, H. (2011) Host plants and larvae of two sawfly species of the Pamphilius sylvaticus group (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) in Japan. Bulletin of the National Museum of Nature and Science, Tokyo, Series A, 37, 27 - 33." type="journal article" year="2011">Shinohara &amp; Kojima 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
